} The process of receiving funds via an on-chain address is trustless and uses a submarine swap. This means there are two ways to spend the sent funds: Either by a preimage that is exposed when the Lightning payment is completed - this is the positive case where the swap was successful. Or by your node when the swap didn't complete within a certain timeout (216 blocks) - this is the negative case where your node will execute a refund (funds become refundable after 288 blocks). Refund will also be available in case the amount sent wasn't within the limits.

